%I A076696 #13 Jul 15 2026 20:30:35
%S A076696 1,2,8,3,7,21,4,5,6,30,9,10,12,15,18
%N A076696 Triangle read by rows: n-th row contains n numbers whose product is a square; all numbers in triangle are distinct.
%C A076696 Second solution. Both solutions are smaller than A076031.
%H A076696 Johann Cigler, <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Johann-Cigler/publication/408731838">Weights of bounded Dyck paths which are related to q-Narayana polynomials</a>, ResearchGate, Univ. Vienna (Austria 2026). See p. 12.
%e A076696 1^2 4^2 21^2 60^2 540^2 = (1)(2 8)(3 7 21)(4 5 6 30)(9 10 12 15 18)
%Y A076696 Cf. A076031, A076596.
%K A076696 more,nonn,tabl,obsc,changed
%O A076696 1,2
%A A076696 _Donald S. McDonald_, Nov 10 2002
%E A076696 It is not clear to me how one decides what numbers to place in the n-th row! - _N. J. A. Sloane_, Nov 30 2002
